# Verify before done

Do not mark a task complete until verification passes for every file you created or edited.

**`npm run verify` proves the build and existing tests pass; it does not prove the change is correct.** After verify is green, run the **logic review** below for the kind of change you made.

## Required steps (end of each round)

Follow [`.cursor/skills/pre-handoff/SKILL.md`](../skills/pre-handoff/SKILL.md) (also [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md)).

1. **Automated gate** — Use the **Shell** tool to run **`npm run pre-handoff`** (lint + typecheck + full unit tests). Fix until exit 0. The project **stop hook** blocks agent completion until this passes when watched paths changed.
2. **IDE diagnostics** — Call `ReadLints` on all touched paths. Fix every **error**; fix **warnings** you introduced.
3. **Logic review** — Complete the table below (mandatory after step 1 passes).

Individual commands when debugging: `npm run lint`, `npm run typecheck`, `npm test -- --run`.

## Logic review (after verify is green)

Skim changed code and explicitly answer **yes/no** for each item that applies. If any answer is “might be wrong,” add a test or fix before finishing.

| Area | Ask |
|------|-----|
| **RxJS + session** | Does `filter` run *before* `distinctUntilChanged`? Logout (`null`) must be visible to dedupe so re-login with the same email still emits. |
| **Cache** | Every write path has a matching **invalidate** (logout, admin map/unmap, account switch). Stale reads if invalidation depends only on in-memory arrays. |
| **Async races** | In-flight requests: ignore or cancel when `loadedEmail` / route / session changes mid-flight. |
| **Empty vs missing** | Distinguish “no list id” vs “list id but empty members / API error” — UI and filters must not show stale data from the other case. |
| **Angular DI** | New service injections: no cycle (`providedIn: 'root'` services importing each other). Prefer lazy `Injector.get` on logout/edge paths if needed. |
| **OnPush / signals** | State updated in subscribe/async paths calls `markForCheck()` or uses signals so UI updates. |
| **Bug fixes** | Same round: **regression test** that fails without the fix (not only “method was called”). |

## If verification fails

- Do not summarize success or stop with known failures.
- Fix or revert, then re-run until green.

## Scope

- Prefer `npm run verify` over ad-hoc partial test files unless the user asked for a single spec only.
- New/changed behavior needs matching spec updates in the same round.
- For non-trivial behavior changes, add a **regression test** for the reported bug class, not only happy-path coverage.

## Optional: second pass before PR / review agent

Ask the agent: **“Self-review this diff against verify-before-done logic review; list risks and add tests for any gap.”**  
Or run your review agent on the branch after `npm run verify` is green — it catches logic issues CI cannot.
